Credit Agricole Egypt Surges Most in a Year After Dividend

-- B y   A l a a   S h a h i n e
-- 
2011-04-03T13:16:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-03/credit-agricole-egypt-surges-most-in-a-year-after-dividend.html
Credit Agricole Egypt SAE (CIEB) , the
third-largest publicly traded bank in the North African nation,
surged the most in a year after saying it will pay a dividend of
1.2 Egyptian pounds ($0.20) a share.  Shares advanced 5 percent, the most since April 2010, to
11.97 pounds at the 2:30 p.m. close in Cairo. Shares of Credit
Agricole  Egypt  lose the right to the dividend on April 18, the
Cairo-based lender said in a regulatory filing today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alaa Shahine in Dubai at 
 asalha@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
